{"pageProps":{"frontmatter":{"title":"Creating Aliases on a Mac","meta":"Creating Aliases on a Mac is an easy thing to do & can save a lot of time","share_image":"https://yowainwright.imgix.net/icons/os.jpg","categories":["code","terminal"],"date":"May 19, 2016","path":"/creating-aliases-mac"},"content":"<p>Creating Aliases on a Mac is an easy thing to do &#x26; can save a lot of time. When working in Terminal or another command line app, you may want to set up an alias to make your workflows easier.</p>\n<p>To do this you'll want to set up a <code>.bash_profile</code>:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Run <code>vi ~/.bash_profile</code> in your command line app of choice, or [text editor of choice] ~/.bash_profile</li>\n<li>This will open up your <code>bash profile</code> in <code>vi</code> or your <code>text editor</code> to be edited</li>\n</ul>\n<p>If you'd like to use a text editor but don't have one that opens instead of <code>vi</code> checkout this <a href=\"//help.github.com/articles/associating-text-editors-with-git/\">post</a></p>\n<p>Here's a look at part of my <code>.bash_profile</code>:</p>\n<pre class=\"shiki shiki-themes theme-custom-light theme-custom-dark\" style=\"background-color:#f9f9f9;--shiki-dark-bg:#031030;color:#000000;--shiki-dark:#b3d8e5\" tabindex=\"0\"><code><span class=\"line\"></span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color:#6A9955;--shiki-dark:#6A9955\"># -------</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color:#6A9955;--shiki-dark:#6A9955\"># mySQL</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color:#6A9955;--shiki-dark:#6A9955\"># -------</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color:#569CD6;--shiki-dark:#569CD6\">export</span><span style=\"color:#007CF0;--shiki-dark:#007CF0\"> PATH</span><span style=\"color:#E194B5;--shiki-dark:#E194B5\">=</span><span style=\"color:#000000;--shiki-dark:#B3D8E5\">/</span><span style=\"color:#007CF0;--shiki-dark:#007CF0\">usr</span><span style=\"color:#000000;--shiki-dark:#B3D8E5\">/</span><span style=\"color:#007CF0;--shiki-dark:#007CF0\">local</span><span style=\"color:#000000;--shiki-dark:#B3D8E5\">/</span><span style=\"color:#007CF0;--shiki-dark:#007CF0\">mysql</span><span style=\"color:#000000;--shiki-dark:#B3D8E5\">/</span><span style=\"color:#007CF0;--shiki-dark:#007CF0\">bin</span><span style=\"color:#000000;--shiki-dark:#B3D8E5\">:</span><span style=\"color:#007CF0;--shiki-dark:#007CF0\">$PATH</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"></span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color:#6A9955;--shiki-dark:#6A9955\"># -------</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color:#6A9955;--shiki-dark:#6A9955\"># host setups</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color:#6A9955;--shiki-dark:#6A9955\"># -------</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color:#569CD6;--shiki-dark:#569CD6\">alias</span><span style=\"color:#007CF0;--shiki-dark:#007CF0\"> hosts</span><span style=\"color:#E194B5;--shiki-dark:#E194B5\">=</span><span style=\"color:#007CF0;--shiki-dark:#007CF0\">\"sublime /etc/hosts\"</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color:#569CD6;--shiki-dark:#569CD6\">alias</span><span style=\"color:#007CF0;--shiki-dark:#007CF0\"> vhosts</span><span style=\"color:#E194B5;--shiki-dark:#E194B5\">=</span><span style=\"color:#007CF0;--shiki-dark:#007CF0\">\"sublime /etc/apache2/vhosts\"</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"></span></code></pre>","slug":"creating-aliases-mac"},"__N_SSG":true}